This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it proposes a fully decentralized churn stabilization mechanism for Skip Graphs, which is a distributed hash table (DHT) routing overlay used in peer-to-peer (P2P) systems. It may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it proposes a tool called Sliding Window De Bruijn Graph (SW-DBG) to predict the availability of nodes. Additionally, it may belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as Skip Graphs are used in social networks, and the proposed mechanism aims to improve the overlay connectivity of P2P systems. It may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as it deals with the connectivity of nodes in a network, and the proposed mechanism aims to preserve the overlay connectivity of Skip Graphs. Finally, it may belong to the Performance (cs.PF) sub-category as it evaluates the performance of the proposed mechanism in terms of overlay connectivity and routing speed.
